HEADWORD: Respondentia
<hw>Re`spon*den"ti*a</hw> <pr>(r?`sp?n*d?n"sh?*?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See <er>Respondence</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Commercial Law)</fld> <def>A loan upon goods laden on board a
ship. It differs from <xex>bottomry</xex>, which is a loan on the ship
itself.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

